Angular version of type-ahead
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22459139/making-a-typeahead-with-angularjs

Note: instead of using typeahead, there is another widget to deal with lists:
https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-select

The following works using unmodified versions of the libraries:
http://plnkr.co/edit/bZMEOx0Qwo6VzW7oSuEE?p=preview
  <head>
    <link href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link href="style.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <script src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.2.27/angular.js"></script>
    <script src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/angular-ui-bootstrap/0.12.0/ui-bootstrap-tpls.js"></script>
    <script src="app.js"></script>
  </head>


