5) Dynamic templates:
http://onehungrymind.com/angularjs-dynamic-templates/

6) Provide a global flag, to force the RequisitionsService to work only with pending
requisitions, like provision.pl. On a system with lots of requisitions/nodes that should
accelerate the response time. In theory, there is no need to know if a node has been
deployed or not.

Provisioning Ideas

1) Use a thread pool when reading requisitions to reduce the time spend on the ReST Query

2) Keep the requisitions on a cache to avoid the delay of unmarshaling the XMLs.

3) Create a new ReST end point to return the list of requisitions names, instead of
retrieving all the requisitions for the same purpose. This could use a simple file reader
and a SQL query to build the statistics (deployed/pending).

